 string; quantity: number; unitPrice: number }>`\n   - `customerId: string`\n\n3. **OrderCancelledEvent** (extends OrderEvent)\n   - `reason: string`\n\n4. **OrderRefundedEvent** (extends OrderEvent)\n   - `amount: number`\n\n5. **PaymentChargedEvent** (extends OrderEvent)\n   - `amount: number`\n   - `paymentMethod: string`\n\n6. **StockReservedEvent** (extends OrderEvent)\n   - `items: Array<{ productId: string; quantity: number }>`\n\n**Constants:**\n- `ORDER_EVENTS` object with event names:\n  - `CREATED: 'order.created'`\n  - `CONFIRMED: 'order.confirmed'`\n  - `CANCELLED: 'order.cancelled'`\n  - `REFUNDED: 'order.refunded'`\n  - `PAYMENT_CHARGED: 'order.payment.charged'`\n  - `STOCK_RESERVED: 'order.stock.reserved'`\n  - `STOCK_RELEASED: 'order.stock.released'`\n  - `NOTIFICATION_SENT: 'order.notification.sent'`\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/events/bus.ts\n**Purpose:** Central event bus for pub-sub messaging\n\n**Type:**\n- `EventHandler = (data: unknown) => void | Promise<void>`\n\n**Global State:**\n- `globalHandlers: Map<string, EventHandler[]>` — Module-level registry shared across all EventBus instances\n\n**Class: EventBus**\n\nMethods:\n1. **on(event: string, handler: EventHandler): void**\n   - Registers a handler for an event\n   - Adds handler to global registry\n\n2. **off(event: string, handler: EventHandler): void**\n   - Removes a specific handler from an event\n   - Filters handler from global registry\n\n3. **async emit(event: string, data: unknown): Promise<void>**\n   - Emits an event to all registered handlers\n   - Awaits all handlers sequentially\n   - Handlers execute in registration order\n\n4. **clear(): void**\n   - Clears all handlers from global registry\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/orders/repository.ts\n**Purpose:** In-memory repository for order persistence\n\n**Type: OrderStatus**\n- Union type: `'pending' | 'confirmed' | 'cancelled' | 'refunded'`\n\n**Interface: OrderItem**\n- `productId: string`\n- `quantity: number`\n- `unitPrice: number`\n\n**Interface: Order**\n- `id: string`\n- `customerId: string`\n- `items: OrderItem[]`\n- `status: OrderStatus`\n- `total: number`\n- `discount: number`\n- `taxRate: number`\n- `createdAt: number`\n- `updatedAt: number`\n- `notes?: string` (optional)\n\n**Class: OrderRepository**\n\nPrivate State:\n- `store: Map<string, Order>` — In-memory order storage\n\nMethods:\n1. **create(order: Order): Order**\n   - Stores order and returns deep copy\n   - Creates new Order object with spread\n\n2. **findById(id: string): Order | undefined**\n   - Retrieves order by ID\n   - Returns deep copy or undefined\n\n3. **update(id: string, updates: Partial<Order>): Order | undefined**\n   - Merges updates with existing order\n   - Sets `updatedAt` to current timestamp\n   - Returns updated copy or undefined\n\n4. **findByCustomer(customerId: string): Order[]**\n   - Returns all orders for a customer\n   - Returns deep copies\n\n5. **findByStatus(status: OrderStatus): Order[]**\n   - Returns all orders with given status\n   - Returns deep copies\n\n6. **clear(): void**\n   - Clears all orders from store\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/orders/service.ts\n**Purpose:** Business logic for order processing with event emission\n\n**Constants:**\n- `REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS = 30` — Refund window in days\n\n**Class: OrderService**\n\nConstructor Dependencies:\n- `repo: OrderRepository`\n- `eventBus: EventBus`\n- `billingService: BillingService`\n\nMethods:\n\n1. **async createOrder(id: string, customerId: string, items: OrderItem[], discount: number = 0, taxRate: number = 0.1): Promise<Order>**\n   - Creates order with pending status\n   - Emits ORDER_EVENTS.CREATED event\n   - Charges payment via billingService\n   - Updates order status to 'confirmed'\n   - Emits ORDER_EVENTS.CONFIRMED event\n   - Returns confirmed order\n\n2. **async cancelOrder(id: string, reason: string): Promise<Order | undefined>**\n   - Checks if order exists\n   - Returns undefined if not confirmed\n   - Emits ORDER_EVENTS.CANCELLED event (includes items)\n   - Updates status to 'cancelled'\n   - Returns updated order\n\n3. **async refundOrder(id: string): Promise<Order | undefined>**\n   - Checks if order exists and is cancelled\n   - Calculates days since creation\n   - Throws error if beyond 30-day window\n   - Issues refund via billingService\n   - Updates status to 'refunded'\n   - Returns updated order\n\n4. **getOrder(id: string): Order | undefined**\n   - Simple getter for order by ID\n\n5. **getOrdersByCustomer(customerId: string): Order[]**\n   - Wrapper for repo.findByCustomer\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/inventory/repository.ts\n**Purpose:** In-memory repository for stock/inventory management\n\n**Interface: StockRecord**\n- `productId: string`\n- `available: number` — Available quantity\n- `reserved: number` — Reserved/committed quantity\n\n**Class: InventoryRepository**\n\nPrivate State:\n- `store: Map<string, StockRecord>` — Stock storage by productId\n\nMethods:\n\n1. **setStock(productId: string, available: number): void**\n   - Sets available stock for product\n   - Preserves existing reserved stock\n\n2. **getStock(productId: string): StockRecord | undefined**\n   - Retrieves stock record\n   - Returns deep copy or undefined\n\n3. **reserve(productId: string, quantity: number): boolean**\n   - Reserves quantity from available stock\n   - Returns false if insufficient available stock\n   - Decrements available, increments reserved\n   - Returns true if successful\n\n4. **release(productId: string, quantity: number): boolean**\n   - Releases reserved stock back to available\n   - Returns false if insufficient reserved stock\n   - Decrements reserved, increments available\n   - Returns true if successful\n\n5. **clear(): void**\n   - Clears all stock records\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/inventory/service.ts\n**Purpose:** Event-driven inventory management service\n\n**Class: InventoryService**\n\nConstructor Dependencies:\n- `repo: InventoryRepository`\n- `eventBus: EventBus`\n\nMethods:\n\n1. **registerHandlers(): void**\n   - Registers event handlers for CREATED and CANCELLED events\n   - Binds handlers to this context\n\n2. **private async handleOrderCreated(data: unknown): Promise<void>**\n   - Casts data to OrderCreatedEvent\n   - Iterates through items and reserves stock\n   - On failure: rolls back all previous reservations\n   - Throws error with product ID if stock insufficient\n   - Emits ORDER_EVENTS.STOCK_RESERVED event\n\n3. **private async handleOrderCancelled(data: unknown): Promise<void>**\n   - Casts data as OrderCancelledEvent\n   - Checks if event.status is 'cancelled'\n   - Releases reserved stock from event.items\n   - Emits ORDER_EVENTS.STOCK_RELEASED event\n\n4. **setStock(productId: string, quantity: number): void**\n   - Wrapper for repo.setStock\n\n5. **getStock(productId: string): StockRecord | undefined**\n   - Wrapper for repo.getStock\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/billing/calculator.ts\n**Purpose:** Price calculation with discount and tax\n\n**Interface: PriceBreakdown**\n- `subtotal: number`\n- `discountAmount: number`\n- `taxAmount: number`\n- `total: number`\n\n**Function: calculateOrderTotal(items: OrderItem[], discountPercent: number, taxRate: number): PriceBreakdown**\n\nCalculation Logic:\n1. Calculate subtotal: sum of (unitPrice × quantity) for all items\n2. Calculate discount: subtotal × (discountPercent / 100)\n3. Calculate after-discount: subtotal - discountAmount\n4. Calculate tax: afterDiscount × taxRate\n5. Calculate total: afterDiscount + taxAmount\n6. All values rounded to 2 decimal places using Math.round(...) / 100 pattern\n7. Returns breakdown with all computed values\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/billing/service.ts\n**Purpose:** Payment processing and billing event handling\n\n**Interface: PaymentRecord**\n- `orderId: string`\n- `amount: number`\n- `method: string` — Payment method\n- `status: 'charged' | 'refunded'`\n- `processedAt: number` — Timestamp\n\n**Class: BillingService**\n\nConstructor Dependencies:\n- `eventBus: EventBus`\n- `notificationService: NotificationService`\n\nPrivate State:\n- `payments: Map<string, PaymentRecord>` — Payment records by orderId\n\nMethods:\n\n1. **registerHandlers(): void**\n   - Registers handlers for STOCK_RESERVED and REFUNDED events\n   - Binds handlers to this context\n\n2. **private async handleStockReserved(data: unknown): Promise<void>**\n   - Receives stock reserved event\n   - Emits ORDER_EVENTS.PAYMENT_CHARGED event\n   - Amount set to 0 (actual amount set by order service)\n\n3. **async chargePayment(orderId: string, items: OrderItem[], discountPercent: number, taxRate: number, paymentMethod: string): Promise<PaymentRecord>**\n   - Calculates total using calculateOrderTotal\n   - Creates PaymentRecord with status 'charged'\n   - Stores payment record\n   - Calls notificationService.sendConfirmation\n   - Returns payment record\n\n4. **private async handleRefund(data: unknown): Promise<void>**\n   - Receives refund event data\n   - Updates payment status to 'refunded' if exists\n   - Calls notificationService.sendRefundNotice\n\n5. **async issueRefund(orderId: string, amount: number): Promise<PaymentRecord | undefined>**\n   - Retrieves payment record\n   - Updates status to 'refunded'\n   - Emits ORDER_EVENTS.REFUNDED event\n   - Returns updated payment copy\n\n6. **getPayment(orderId: string): PaymentRecord | undefined**\n   - Retrieves payment by orderId\n   - Returns deep copy or undefined\n\n7. **clear(): void**\n   - Clears all payment records\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/src/notifications/service.ts\n**Purpose:** Notification generation and tracking with templates\n\n**Interface: NotificationRecord**\n- `type: string` — Notification type\n- `orderId: string`\n- `message: string`\n- `sentAt: number` — Timestamp\n\n**Class: NotificationService**\n\nPrivate State:\n- `templates: Map<string, string>` — Message templates\n  - `'order.confirmed'`: `'Your order {orderId} has been confirmed. Total: ${total}'`\n  - `'order.cancelled'`: `'Your order {orderId} has been cancelled. Reason: {reason}'`\n  - `'order.refunded'`: `'Your refund of ${amount} for order {orderId} has been processed.'`\n- `sent: NotificationRecord[]` — List of sent notifications\n\nConstructor:\n- Initializes template map\n\nMethods:\n\n1. **sendConfirmation(orderId: string, total: number): NotificationRecord**\n   - Retrieves template\n   - Replaces placeholders: {orderId}, {total}\n   - Creates notification record with type 'confirmation'\n   - Pushes to sent array\n   - Returns notification\n\n2. **sendCancellation(orderId: string, reason: string): NotificationRecord**\n   - Retrieves template\n   - Replaces placeholders: {orderId}, {reason}\n   - Creates notification record with type 'cancellation'\n   - Pushes to sent array\n   - Returns notification\n\n3. **sendRefundNotice(orderId: string, amount: number): NotificationRecord**\n   - Retrieves template\n   - Replaces placeholders: {orderId}, {amount}\n   - Creates notification record with type 'refund'\n   - Pushes to sent array\n   - Returns notification\n\n4. **getSentNotifications(): NotificationRecord[]**\n   - Returns shallow copy of sent array\n\n5. **clear(): void**\n   - Clears sent array\n\n---\n\n## TEST FILES\n\n### /workspace/tests/events.test.ts\n**Test Suite: EventBus**\nTotal Tests: 5\n\n1. **\"emits events to registered handlers\"**\n   - Registers handler for 'test' event\n   - Emits event with { value: 1 }\n   - Verifies handler receives data\n\n2. **\"supports multiple handlers for same event\"**\n   - Registers two handlers for 'test'\n   - Emits event\n   - Verifies both handlers called (count = 2)\n\n3. **\"does not fire handlers for different events\"**\n   - Registers handler for 'other'\n   - Emits 'test' event\n   - Verifies handler not called\n\n4. **\"removes handlers with off()\"**\n   - Registers handler, removes it\n   - Emits event\n   - Verifies handler not called\n\n5. **\"clears all handlers\"**\n   - Registers handlers for events 'a' and 'b'\n   - Calls clear()\n   - Emits both events\n   - Verifies neither handler called\n\n---\n\n### /workspace/tests/orders.test.ts\n**Test Suite: OrderService**\nTotal Tests: 9\n\n1. **\"creates an order and confirms it\"**\n   - Sets inventory: SKU-1 = 10\n   - Creates order: O1, C1, 1x SKU-1 @ $25\n   - Expects: status='confirmed', total=$55 (50 + 10% tax)\n\n2. **\"reserves stock when order is created\"**\n   - Sets inventory: SKU-1 = 10\n   - Creates order: 3x SKU-1 @ $10\n   - Expects: available=7, reserved=3\n\n3. **\"cancels a confirmed order\"**\n   - Sets inventory: SKU-1 = 10\n   - Creates order: 2x SKU-1 @ $10\n   - Cancels order with reason 'changed mind'\n   - Expects: status='cancelled'\n\n4. **\"releases stock when order is cancelled\"**\n   - Sets inventory: SKU-1 = 10\n   - Creates order: 4x SKU-1 @ $10\n   - Cancels order\n   - Expects: available=10, reserved=0 (all released)\n\n5. **\"refuses to cancel a non-confirmed order\"**\n   - Creates and cancels order once\n   - Attempts to cancel again\n   - Expects: returns undefined\n\n6. **\"refunds a cancelled order within 30 days\"**\n   - Sets inventory: SKU-1 = 10\n   - Creates order: 1x SKU-1 @ $100\n   - Cancels and refunds\n   - Expects: status='refunded'\n\n7. **\"allows refund on exactly day 30\"**\n   - Creates order, backdates to 30 days ago\n   - Cancels and refunds\n   - Expects: refund succeeds (status='refunded')\n\n8. **\"rejects refund after 30-day window\"**\n   - Creates order, backdates to 31 days ago\n   - Cancels order, attempts refund\n   - Expects: throws error 'Refund window expired'\n\n**Test Suite: OrderRepository**\nTotal Tests: 4\n\n9. **\"creates and retrieves an order\"**\n   - Creates order O1\n   - Retrieves with findById\n   - Expects: returns same order\n\n10. **\"updates order preserves other fields\"**\n    - Creates order with items, notes\n    - Updates only status\n    - Expects: customerId, notes, items preserved,